    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="132"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d132">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">884.001 Selassie I/377</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 280</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-27">October 27,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>There are enclosed two communications addressed by the President to His Imperial
                    Majesty Haile Selassie I, Emperor of Ethiopia.<note n="38" xml:id="d132fn38"
                        >Dated July 23, and October 23, <ref target="#pg_114">p. 114</ref> and <hi
                            rend="italic">supra</hi>, respectively.</note> It is <pb facs="0128"
                        n="116" xml:id="pg_116"/> desired that these two communications be forwarded
                    by the Legation to the Consul at Asmara, Eritrea, by safe means and that the
                    Legation request the Consul at Asmara to arrange for the transmission of these
                    communications by safe means to the Emperor of Ethiopia at Addis Ababa.<note
                        n="39" xml:id="d132fn39">The letters were delivered to the Emperor on
                        December 3, 1942, by Colonel Clark of the American Mission at Asmara.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sumner Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
